title: Compiler error after upgrading to 1.52 and with CARGO_INCREMENTAL=1

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code Unable to provide a minimum viable code as the error appeared randomly when compiling https://github.com/kdash-rs/kdash after upgrading Rust toolchain to 1.52.0 on Fedora 32. So I ran `cargo clean && cargo run` and it started compiling again. But on subsequent compile with `CARGO_INCREMENTAL=1 cargo run` it fails with same issue. If I run `CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 cargo run` it compiles. SO seems like the issue is when using `CARGO_INCREMENTAL=1` The issue doesnt happen on nightly and beta ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.52.0 (88f19c6da 2021-05-03) binary: rustc commit-hash: 88f19c6dab716c6281af7602e30f413e809c5974 commit-date: 2021-05-03 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.52.0 LLVM version: 12.0.0 ``` ### Error output
